headline: Salesforce (NYSE:CRM) Expands AI Footprint with PepsiCo and UChicago Medicine Collaborations
summary: Salesforce (NYSE:CRM) recently announced two impactful initiatives: PepsiCo's adoption of Agentforce to enhance operational efficiency and customer support, and UChicago Medicine's implementation of Agentforce for Health, aimed at improving patient experiences. These developments underscore the company's commitment to AI integration in diverse industries. Last week, Salesforce's share price rose 4.5%, notably outpacing the broader market's 1.9% climb.
